. This book uncovers ten “forgotten trials” of the Holocaust,selected from the many Nazi trials that have taken place over the course of thelast seven decades. It showcases how perpetrators of the Holocaust were dealtwith in courtrooms around the world, revealing how differentlegal systems responded to the horrors of the Holocaust. The book provides agraphic picture of the genocidal campaign against the Jews through eyewitnesstestimony and incriminating documents and traces how the public memory of theHolocaust was formed over time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945). 0aWar crime trialsxHistoryx20th centuryxEurope. 0aWar crime trialsxHistoryx20th century. 0aWar crime trialsxHistoryy20th century. 0aWar crime trialszEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aWar criminalsxTrials, litigation, etcxEurope. 0aWar criminalszEuropexTrials, litigation, etc. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh1 aTuerkheimer, Frank M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479849932.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479849932423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479849932/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles